modules.description: Provides functions for managing cluster membership updates and log compaction in a distributed system. Operates on data structures such as log entries, node identifiers, and configuration snapshots. Enables efficient state synchronization during leader elections and membership reconfiguration.

Manages distributed consensus by tracking leader nodes, current state, and cluster configuration. Processes log entries through an apply_log function that updates state based on node ID and log index. Used to initialize and maintain a fault-tolerant replicated log system.
